{"TopicId":169343,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.3.X] Kerbal Mass Simulator for External Seat","CreatedByName":"RobotSquid","CreatedById":166311,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-07T11:53:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RobotSquid","CreatedById":166311,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-07T11:53:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdds a button in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E to add the mass of a Kerbal to the External Command Seat. That\u0027s it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022//imgur.com/a/lzDg2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAlbum a/lzDg2 will appear when post is submitted\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMass added is temporary and doesn\u0027t stick around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnjoy accurate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E and mass representations!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/1638/Kerbal%20Mass%20Simulator%20for%20External%20Chair\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EDownload from SpaceDock\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://pastebin.com/FmvKfpXZ\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESource Code\u003C/a\u003E under the MIT License\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-01-07T17:57:10Z\u0022 title=\u002201/07/2018 05:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 7, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by RobotSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EFixed album\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-07T14:29:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166311-robotsquid/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022166311\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166311-robotsquid/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RobotSquid\u003C/a\u003E ! Welcome to the forums!!\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022M83q2jo.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u002226\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/M83q2jo.gif\u0022 style=\u0022width:32px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u002236\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like to inform you that \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/154851-add-on-posting-rules-november-24-2017/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ethere are some requirements\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E for addons, namely \u003Cstrong\u003Eyou must pick and state the license, and provide link to source code\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\nUntil then, I must unfortunately remove the links. Feel free to re-add them once this issue is done with.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, may I suggest adding a few pictures of it in action to help boost its popularity? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou can use the free imgur.com service and then just edit your original post and paste the direct URL to image here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts also possible to resize the image by Ctrl\u002BRMB click and selecting \u0022Edit\u0022 in context menu during edit of your post.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnjoy your stay and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KRsufOoNOIQ\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Efly safe\u003C/a\u003E ! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-01-07T15:50:14Z\u0022 title=\u002201/07/2018 03:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 7, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbal101\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-12T21:54:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat idea and will save me using odd parts stuck on a craft as test weights.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately I just don\u0027t see the right click option.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI installed via \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E and it seems to be installed OK, assuming its just SimulateKerbal.dll in\u00A0GameData/SimulateKerbal folder.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}